<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Malicious" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Malicious,</orth> 1) malignant, malevolent, prone to do mischief: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.83" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.536" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 536</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 5, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 100</bibl>.<lb />2) full of hate: <cit><quote>commander of this hot m. day,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.314" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 314</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>